{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-14T01:33:19Z", "url": "https://livefromalounge.com/visa-launches-meet-greet-for-visa-infinite-cardholders-in-india/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-14T01:33:19Z", "content": "Visa has recently introduced a “Visa Meet &amp; Greet” service in India, aiming to enhance the travel experience for Visa cardholders by offering personalised airport assistance. The service launched… [+2474 chars]", "title": "Visa launches Meet & Greet for Visa Infinite Cardholders in India", "fullContent": "Visa has recently introduced a “Visa Meet & Greet” service in India, aiming to enhance the travel experience for Visa cardholders by offering personalised airport assistance. The service launched just a short while ago.\n\nVisa Meet & Greet\n\nThe Visa Meet & Greet service is provided for those with an eligible India-issued Visa Infinite Credit Card. Eligibility here means USD 1000 (approximately INR 85,000) spent in the past 12 months on point-of-sale transactions outside of India (e-commerce not included).\n\nThe complimentary offer is valid only for international meet-and-greet service (Departure / Arrival) at participating airports within India and is limited to one complimentary visit per calendar year. Here are the airports where it is being offered:\n\nMumbai\n\nAhmedabad\n\nJaipur\n\nGuwahati\n\nLucknow\n\nMangalore\n\nTrivandrum\n\nDelhi\n\nHyderabad\n\nGoa\n\nBangalore\n\nThe service is being offered in alliance with Adani Digital Labs, Pranaam handles Adani Airports, and Encalm handles Delhi, Mumbai, and Goa. For the first step, you need to input your phone number and then your Visa Infinite Card details to validate, and then you will be able to place a request.\n\nFor other instances, or more than one guest, you get a 10% discount on their services. Here are the confirmation timelines.\n\nBottomline\n\nVisa has now introduced a new meet-and-greet service at major Indian airports, arguably as a retort to American Express’s similar service for booking through their Platinum card in India. The service is offered complimentary one time during a year, subject to USD 1000 spend outside of India in Card Present Transactions\n\nWhat do you make of the new meet & greet offered by Visa?\n\nLiked our articles and our efforts? Please pay an amount you are comfortable with; an amount you believe is the fair price for the content you have consumed. Please enter an amount in the box below and click on the button to pay; you can use Netbanking, Debit/Credit Cards, UPI, QR codes, or any Wallet to pay. Every contribution helps cover the cost of the content generated for your benefit.\n\n(Important: to receive confirmation and details of your transaction, please enter a valid email address in the pop-up form that will appear after you click the ‘Pay Now’ button. For international transactions, use Paypal to process the transaction.)\n\nWe are not putting our articles behind any paywall where you are asked to pay before you read an article. We are asking you to pay after you have read the article if you are satisfied with the quality and our efforts."}
